name: Lily V
text: This is our second pizza ranch we've visited this year.  This location was much nicer,  it's the little details that made the difference.  There was a potato soup,  ice cream,  plastic bibs for babies,  even the restroom had extra amenities.  Of course the food was good and staff was friendly.

name: Michele Van Leur
text: Good variety.  Buffet.  Food fresh.  Lots of choices.  Nicest salad bar in a 5 county area. Price reasonable.

name: Darlene Nedved
text: The owner was baking pizzas and offering help to customers on this crazy busy day of the arts festival in the park. Food was fresh, hot, and delicious. Something new to try every time we went back to the buffet.  Owner even gave us directions when we asked. Great service.

name: dax
text: I am a delivery driver for pizza ranch, I've been here for a while and I enjoy it. I also eat here very often, the food is great.

name: Roxanne Snow
text: Everything was very good. I highly recommend this place. Great chicken!

My drink was gone as well as my daughter's food. The employees should make sure someone isn't gone before clearing the table. I didn't pay $12 to only eat 1 plate of food.

The only thing about it is that they don't have toppings for the ice cream. But its good enough on its own! Also it is reasonable pricing for how good it is.

text: Really good buffet including customer selected pizza choices and some of the best fried chicken I've ever tasted.  And the dessert streusel pizza, WOW, that is some tasty stuff!.  Pizza was always hot, staff very friendly and helpful, I'll eat here again I'm sure next time in Brookings.
